spend $100 million in Zambia to boost agricultural production
and reduce poverty during the next five years, the  Post
reported , citing Mark Storella, the U.S. envoy to Zambia.  The money will be spent through the U.S. Agency for
International Development, the Lusaka-based newspaper said. It
